Assignment: CLI App Testing
•	Use different linux distro containers to check curl cli tool version
•	Use two different terminal windows to start bash in both centos:7 and ubuntyu:14.04, using -it
•	Learn the docker container –rm option so you can save cleanup
•	Ensure curl is installed on latest version for that distro
o	Ubuntu: apt-get update && apt-get install curl
o	Centos: yum update curl

docker container run --rm -it centos:7 bash
yum update curl
curl --version
#then exit and container should be deleted
 
 For Ubuntu
 docker container run --rm -it ubuntu:14.04 bash
 apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl
 curl --version
 #then exit and container should be deleted. This is --rm does for us.
 
